-- Oracle, Wipro Considering Acquiring Stakes in Sonata Software, DNA Reports
-- B y   J e r a n   W i t t e n s t e i n
-- 2010-10-31T23:47:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-31/oracle-wipro-may-buy-stakes-in-sonata-software-dna-reports.html
Oracle Corp. and Wipro Infotech are
considering buying stakes in India’s Sonata Software, Daily News
& Analysis reported, citing unidentified people familiar with
the situation.  An unidentified spokesperson for Wipro said the report was
“market speculation,” according to DNA. Oracle declined to
comment, the report said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jeran Wittenstein at 
 jwittenstei1@bloomberg.net  